== Carrot Rice ==

Fill a large #saucepan{} with the boiling water and bring back to the boil on
high heat.

When boiling, add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{8-10%minutes}, then
drain in a #sieve{} and set aside.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed, no need to peel) and coarsely grate.

Halve the @avocado{1} lengthways and twist apart. Remove the stone, scoop out
the flesh and chop into chunks.

Roughly chop the @coriander{1 bunch}(chopped, stalks and all). Zest the
@lime{1} then chop into wedges. Halve the @red chilli{1/2}(deseeded and finely
chopped) lengthways, deseed and finely chop.

== Thai Dressing ==

In a #small bowl{}, stir together the @soy sauce{25%ml}, @honey{15%g} and the
juice of half the lime.

Season to taste with @salt{}, @ground black pepper{} and a pinch of @sugar{}

== Prawns ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat.

When hot, add the @king prawns{120} and stir-fry for ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the centre.

== Assembly ==

Toss the cooked rice into a #mixing bowl{} with the grated carrot.

Stir through half the coriander, all the lime zest and a pinch of chilli.

Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed.

Serve the rice in bowls topped with the prawns, chunks of avocado and a
sprinkling of remaining coriander and red chilli (go easy on the chilli if you
don't like things too hot!).

Drizzle the dressing all over and top with the remaining lime wedges for
squeezing over.